How do you prevent event propagation in LWC?
Companies that asked this: KPMG, Salesforce, TCS, IBM, Accenture, Infosys

Answer:
Event propagation in LWC can be prevented using standard DOM methods: stopPropagation() and preventDefault().

Methods:

event.stopPropagation() - Stops event from bubbling up to parent elements

event.preventDefault() - Prevents default browser behavior (like form submission)

Example:

We have a parent component that contains a child component with a form. When the user clicks the Submit button:

The child stops the event from bubbling.

It also prevents the default form submission behavior.

parentComponent.html

<template>
    <div onclick={handleParentClick} style="border: 2px solid blue; padding: 20px;">
        <h2>Parent Component</h2>
        <c-child-component></c-child-component>
    </div>
</template>
parentComponent.js

import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';
 
export default class ParentComponent extends LightningElement {
    handleParentClick() {
        console.log('Parent: Click event received');
        alert('Parent received click â€” bubbling worked!');
    }
}
childComponent.html

<template>
    <form onsubmit={handleSubmit}>
        <h3>Child Component</h3>
        <input type="text" placeholder="Type something..." />
        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
</template>
childComponent.js

import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';
 
export default class ChildComponent extends LightningElement {
    handleSubmit(event) {
        event.preventDefault();       // ðŸ”’ Prevents form from reloading the page
        event.stopPropagation();      // ðŸ”• Prevents bubbling to parent
 
        console.log('Child: Form submitted');
        alert('Child handled form submit. No bubbling, no reload.');
    }
}
